Model-implied moments for a penfa object

fitted-penfa-method.Rd

An S4 method returning the model-implied moments for an object of class penfa. For every group, a list with the model-implied moments is returned: cov contains the implied covariance matrix, and mean the implied mean vector. If just the covariance matrix is analyzed, only the cov argument is returned.

# S4 method for penfa
fitted(object, labels = TRUE)

Arguments

object

An object of class penfa, found as a result of a call to penfa.
labels

Logical. If TRUE, the model-implied moments are named according to the item names used in the model syntax.

See also

penfa, penfa-class

Examples


## --- Continuing the Examples from penfa manual page:
require(utils)
example("penfa", echo = FALSE)
